CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 11, 1959, pg.1 reads: "As Pittsburgh Played Host to the All-Stars - Old Friends - Vic Power of the Cleveland Indians and Orlando Cepeda of the San Francisco Giants had plenty to talk about before the start of the All-Star game. Both are from Puerto Rico and are good friends.  Each also does a great job of playing first base. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Cleveland Indians baseball player no. 10 Vic Power with bat, posing with San Francisco Giants player Orlando Cepeda with glove, with reporters in background, Forbes Field, possibly for All Star Game
